Anyone else having reliability issues with the V2 versions of the SPARK MAX CAN Cable V2 (REV-11-1880)?

So far I have had two cable assembles where the doubled up wires have slipped out of the pins.

I extracted both pins and there were no strands in them, so the wires did not break.
The insulation on the wires does not look like it was crimped by the strain relief part of the pin.

Then I extracted the still attached wires. With the two wires per pin, the top most wire is barely in crimp. Only about have the strands were captured. Neither of the wires were crimped by the strain relief part of the pin.

It seems that the pins are not designed for two wires and instead of adding reliability this V2 is now a liability.

Any thoughts? A bad batch or a bad idea?

Bill FRC871
